	<div class="single_story">
		<div class="story_body">
		    <html><body><p>Larry Lucchino, President and <span class="caps">CEO</span> of the Boston Red Sox since 2002, will step down from his posts at the end of the season. His contract is set to expire then and he will not seek to renew&nbsp;it. </p><p>Under his tenure, the Red Sox won their first World Series in 86 years in 2004. He also oversaw World Series victories in 2007 and 2013 with Boston, and 1983 with the Baltimore Orioles. <br/></p></body></html>
		</div>
